description: 16-page free comic book produced by Remington Arms Company Inc.

When Sarah is thrown into prison along with a young woman from the Church of Teresu, she gets an earful of religion. But when Sarah finds the girls selling their bodies to the troops for a few boxes of military rations, she resolves to have a word with their spiritual leader.

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: Sarah's heart is troubled. The more she finds out about the Church of Saint Teresu, the more she is angered by the brutal way it exploits the young women who belong to it. And there is one girl who will not leave her mind. Has she finally found her missing daughter? But unbeknownst to Sarah or the death-obsessed Saint Teresu, other forces are closing in. The commander of the garrison has decided the church is undermining the morale of his soldiers, and he's ready to take steps to put an end to it.

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: Some people are born under a lucky star. Among the battered and abused orphan girls serving Mother Teres, Satoko is one of the lucky ones. The tall, strong woman waiting outside the church doors is Sarah, her mother, rewarded at last after ten years of searching for her long-lost daughter. But the joy of reunion is brief. Ten years have scarred both mother and daughter, and before they can even begin to heal the wounds, the armored forces of Mother Earth open their final assault on the refugee-clogged town, and the Church of Mother Teres is in the way!

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: Shells are raining down on the church of Mother Teres, and one of the victims is Athena's baby daughter Meena. When Mother Teres tells the young woman to let her baby die rather than live on in a world of carnage and slaughter, Sarah takes charge. With Athena and Satoko at her side, they go in search of medicine. But the town has been hit even harder than the church. And one of the victims is Sarah's traveling companion Tsue!

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: Amid the wreckage caused by shelling, further chaos ensues as the unity under the Church of Teres begins to crumble. Mother Teres is called before the army officials. While she is under questioning, the soldiers continue to abuse the girls of the Church. It is up to Sarah to end this depravity and free the girls from their exploitation.

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: Satoko is pregnant by her young soldier lover, and now Mother Teresu wants her to abort the baby. But if war has been hard on Satoko and her friends, it's about to get worse. As an object lesson to other pacifists, the commander of the Epoch base has come up with an idea. He's going to put them all, including Sarah, in the front trenches of the final defenses of the city. And let them see first hand what war is all about.

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: Mother Teres succeeds in her suicide run. Tortured by the thought of all the things she has done to the girls under her charge, she choses death. But, the horror is not over -- the commander is ordering the girls to stand as a human shield in front of the army defenses!

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: War is hell, and the approaching tank brigade is not going to stop its advance for a group of young nuns praying to heaven for help. When the brigade tries to open a path through the minefields, and sets off a chain reaction that turns the entire battlefield into a blinding sea of detonations, can anyone, even Sarah's daughter, survive the conflagration?

volume.name: The Legend of Mother Sarah: City of the Angels

description: LILITH--the legendary first wife of Adam and the demon queen of the night. Lilith demanded equality from her husband, but when she found that she could not have it, she denounced the name of god and banished herself from the garden forever. It's the year 2000--Mardi Gras in the infamous city of sin ...New Orleans. The magical night of debauchery and excess has brought a plague upon the women of the city. Lilith has returned and she will have her revenge on mankind. LILI. Written by 1999 EISNER nominee Brian Michael Bendis (Sam and Twitch, Jinx, Torso), with stunning artwork from the exceptional team of The Waltrip Brothers, this totally original one-shot of modern mythological horror is a must-read!

It's the 23rd Century, and at age 21... your life is over. Bluewater Comics proudly presents a new adaptation of William F. Nolan's masterpiece of dystopian future: Logan's Run! Logan-6 has been trained to kill; born and bred from conception to be the best of the best, but his time is short, and before his life ends he's got one final mission: Find and destroy 'Sanctuary', a fabled haven for those that chose to defy the system. But when Logan meets and falls in love with Jessica, he begins to question the very system he swore to protect and soon they're both running for their lives. Featuring a foreword by Logan's Run co-creator George Clayton Johnson.

name: Shattered Time, Part 2

description:
Lanfeust, an apprentice blacksmith, is asked to mend the sword of Knight Gold-Azure. When handling the sword's pommel Lanfeust gains the power to use any power known in Troy, more so without the presence of a sage.

Nicolede, the local sage, decides to take Lanfeust to the conservatory of Eckmül, to learn more about this powers. C'ian, Nicolede's daughter and Lanfeusts fiancé accompanies them, as well as her younger sister Cixi, who secretly is in love with Lanfeust. Very soon they meet a wandering Troll, Hebus. Nicolede enchantes him so he can serve as their body-guard.
name: L'ivoire du Magohamoth

description: Lanfeusts party and a somewhat unwilling Knight Gold-Azure arrive at Eckmül. The sages at the conservatory are not that surprised of Lanfeusts power, because a previous sage (Thanos) had the same abilities. Because the other sages suspected he was going to abuse his powers, they forced Thanos to leave Eckmül. Thanos took up piracy. Nicolede feels he has done his duties and returns home with his daughters while Lanfeust stays behind at the conservatory. Then news arrives that Thanos has captured Nicolede and C'ian...
name: Thanos The Pirate

description: Cixi has told Thanos about the ivory in the sword of Knight Gold-Azure to save Lanfeusts life. Thanos is determined to get his hands on the sword. Lanfeust and his friends succeed in escaping from the pirates and travel to Gold-Azure castle. The castle however is besieged by Baron Avveroës.
name: The Gold-Azure Castle

description: Lanfeust has broken the siege of Gold-Azure castle by defeating Baron Avveroës. Knight Gold-Azure however is not at the castle, but is participating in the tournament of Culhaig. Lanfeust and his friends travel to the tournament and final catch up with Knigh Gold-Azure. But Baron Avveroës is also present and wants revenge...
name: The Palladin Of Eckmül

description: After killing Baron Avveroës (who was in reality Thanos) at the tournament of Culhaig, Lanfeust, Cixi, C'ian, Nicolede and Hebus have returned to Eckmül with the sword of Knight Gold-Azure. They all enjoy Lanfeust powers. He conjures a house in the hills, fashionable clothes and gifts for the girls, even a white dragon for Cixi. A bored Cixi makes more and more demands and Lanfeust finally agrees to throw a party. Unfortunately Thanos is not dead and one of his accomplices is preparing a trap at the party...
name: The Thrill Of The Haruspice

description:
Thanos has stolen the sword of Knight Gold-Azure and used his powers to conqueror Eckmül and the surroundings. Lanfeust and his friends managed to escape and are given shelter at Darshan. The emperor of Drashan realizes that only Lanfeust can prevent Thanos from invading his country. He helps them to travel to the Palace of the Gods where Nicolede hopes he can find a clue to the home of the Magohamoth. Cixi who tried to seduce Lanfeust is punished by her father and has to stay behind. She is so angry that she decides to join Thanos.

To read the whole story of how Cixi fled Darshan an became Empress of Eckmül you need to read the spin-off Cixi Of Troy.
name: Empress Cixi

description: The Gods of Darshan decided to help Lanfeust and his friends. Sfax guides them to the City of Ice where Nicoled hopes to find new clues to the whereabouts of the Magohamoth. Meanwhile Thanos has imprisoned all the sages while a vigilante called "the shadowy shadow" is defying Thanos' forces at Eckmül. Knight Gold-Azure admits to himself that he is in love with C'ian and decides to look for her. Lanfeust, Nicolede, C'ian and Hebus follow a new lead that brings them to the petaur graveyard.
name: The Petaur Graveyard

description: Final part of this serie. Cixi is revealed to be the shadowy shadow and joined the resistance of Eckmül, while Lanfeust, C’ian, Hebus et Nicolede are still searching for the Magohamoth. They are joined by Knight Gold-Azure who pledges his love for C'ian. Will they find the magical beast and even more important can he help Lanfeust in defeating Thanos?
name: The Fabulous Beast

description: After an absence of 16 year, in which Lanfeust (and Hebus) only aged 1 year (due to the space travel in Lanfeust of the Stars), our hero returns to Troy. A lot of things have changed eg. women are allowed at the conservatory of Eckmül. Due to the absence of Nicolede (visting Gold-Azure) another despot rules Eckmül...
name: L'énigme Or-Azur - 1re partie

description: Orginal Title : Le Banni d'Eckmül
name: Le banni d'Eckmül

description: A new story! Not available in the newspapers! Only in a comic book! This is a major event for girl-watchers everywhere as Brandy attends a wedding... her own! Okay, so she's not marrying you, monkeyboy! But here's your chance to see just who the lucky guy is! And this is also a great place to start reading Liberty Meadows. Why? Because of the great humor? The wild situations? The gorgeous artwork? Well duh! All that, and because Frank Cho recaps his years of stories, bringing new and old readers up to speed and ready for the wedding! So prepare to see all your favorite characters wearing their best clothes and get a few hints on where Frank Cho's epic story will be going in the years to come!

description: Winner of the Xeric Award in 2010 and included in Houghton Mifflin's Best American Comics of 2011, The Pterodactyl Hunters (in the Gilded City) tells the story of Eamon and Declan Sullivan, young members of New York City's Pterodactyl Patrol, a municipal organization protecting the city from the menacing pterodactyls that plague its evening hours. As the New York City of 1904 moves into the modern era, only a few vicious pterosaurs remain. While Eamon makes headlines eradicating the final beasts, young Declan faces a future without the pterodactyl infestation, and without his anticipated role in a new generation of Pterodactyl Hunters.

volume.name: Pterodactyl Hunters in the Gilded City
